Interface Search

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GraphPAP, GraphService, MemGraphSearch, Neo4jSearch, SQLSearch

    public interface Search
    Search provides a method to search for nodes in an NAC graph.

    • Method Detail

      • search

        java.util.HashSet<NodeContext> search(java.lang.String name,
                                      java.lang.String type,
                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> properties)
                               throws PMException
        Search an NGAC graph for nodes matching the given parameters. A node must contain all properties provided to be returned. To get all the nodes that have a specific property key with any value use "*" as the value in the parameter. (i.e. {key=*})
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the nodes to search for.
        type - The type of the nodes to search for.
        properties - The properties of the nodes to search for.
        Returns:
        A set of nodes that match the given search criteria.
        Throws:
        PMException
